-- Euro Pares Gain Versus Dollar as Draghi Sees ‘Downside Risks’
-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 2012-06-06T12:35:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/euro-pares-gain-versus-dollar-as-draghi-sees-downside-risks-.html
The euro pared its gain against the
dollar after European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi  said
the economic outlook has “increased downside risks.”  The 17-nation currency was 0.2 percent higher at $1.2481 at
1:34 p.m. London time, after strengthening to as high as
$1.2528. The euro rose 0.7 percent against the yen to 98.74.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucy Meakin in London at 
